{
  "metadata": {
    "intent": "Detrital-pathway WIRING / REGRESSION test (issue #311; reframed #328). A sessile decomposer is seeded on a standing carcass deposit with NO living agent inside its consumption reach, so its diet is detrital from tick 0 BY CONSTRUCTION. A producer source sits well outside that reach, sustaining a living producer->carcass ecology around the decomposer. This verifies the producer->carcass->decomposer code path closes end to end (energy and nutrient route through detritivory), so detrital_share > 0.5 holds by geometry on every seed. It is NOT evidence that detritivory emerges from dynamics — the diet is forced detrital because the geometry forbids anything else. Emergence evidence comes from the genesis search (decomposers emerge readily from random worlds), not from this file; a dedicated genesis-emergence regression is a deferred follow-up.",
    "source_issue": 311,
    "roster": "1 sessile decomposer (origin, heterotrophy-dominant) on a seeded 8-carcass deposit; 16 producers on a wide ring (radius ~30) well outside the decomposer's reach.",
    "probes": "energy_death",
    "prediction": "live",
    "rationale": "The decomposer physically cannot predate: with body_reach_coefficient = 0 its reach is structure-independent at heterotrophy x contact_range_coefficient = 0.5 x 1.0 = 0.5 world units, and the nearest living agent (the producer ring at radius ~30, toroidal extent 100) is far outside it. So every unit of energy the decomposer drains comes from carcasses -> detrital_share is high by definition. The large seeded deposit (8 carcasses x 60 energy = 480) is sized to outlast max_ticks as the sustaining backstop, while the out-of-reach producer ring reproduces and self-thins, raining carcasses across the field to demonstrate the living producer->carcass->decomposer pathway rather than a sterile pile.",
    "geometry": "Decomposer reach = eff_heterotrophy x (contact_range_coefficient + body_reach_coefficient x sqrt(structure)). body_reach_coefficient is set to 0.0 precisely so reach does not grow with the decomposer's structure: reach stays fixed at 0.5 units and the 'no living agent in reach' property is exact, not approximate. Producers sit at radius ~30 with modest dispersal (4.0), so offspring establish near the ring and toroidal distance to the origin (max 70.7 on a 100-extent torus) keeps them out of the 0.5-unit reach across the full seed sweep.",
    "sustaining_supply": "Large seeded carcass deposit (480 energy) at the decomposer's position as the deterministic, seed-independent backstop that outlasts 2000 ticks; the out-of-reach producer ring supplies the living end of the pathway. The decomposer never depends on inward carcass-fall reaching it, so the detrital-share property is robust regardless of where producer offspring fall.",
    "status": "current — every WorldParameter is specified explicitly (example4 template, post-#309); body_reach_coefficient deliberately 0.0 for exact geometry."
  },
